title: Introduction to C Programming
description: C has been used to develop operating systems (e.g., Unix and Linux), embedded systems (e.g., microcontrollers), and a wide variety of applications, including games, compilers, and system utilities. Learning C programming provides a solid foundation for understanding computer architecture, memory management, and programming in general. However, it also requires careful attention to detail and manual memory management, which can be challenging for beginners.

title: Introduction to Algorithms
